01:26.127 --> 01:27.086
IT'S OKAY.

01:27.170 --> 01:28.046
GO AWAY, TOADIES.

01:28.129 --> 01:30.632
{\an5}All:
OH, YES SIR, OH,
WE'RE OUT OF HERE.

01:30.715 --> 01:33.343
FINALLY, IT'S OVER.

01:33.426 --> 01:37.180
893 EPISODES OF <i> THE FATHEADS.</i>

01:37.263 --> 01:38.807
NOW I CAN FINALLY
CREATE SOMETHING

01:38.890 --> 01:42.018
OF REAL MEANING AND IMPORTANCE.

01:42.101 --> 01:45.522
{\an1}HERE IT IS, THE FINAL EPISODE
OF <i> THE FATHEADS.</i>

01:45.605 --> 01:46.940
OH, GIMME, GIMME, GIMME.

01:47.023 --> 01:48.525
OOH, OOH.

01:48.608 --> 01:51.194
AND WHERE DO YOU
THINK YOU'RE GOING?

01:51.277 --> 01:52.028
{\an1}HUH?

01:52.111 --> 01:53.988
Both:
YOU OWE US A PILOT

01:54.072 --> 01:55.698
FOR ANOTHER SHOW.

01:55.782 --> 01:56.741
WHAT?

01:56.825 --> 01:58.368
JUST CHECK
YOUR CONTRACT.

01:58.451 --> 02:00.370
YOU'LL SEE
WE GET ONE MORE SHOW

02:00.453 --> 02:01.496
BEFORE WE LET YOU GO.

02:01.579 --> 02:02.872
BUT, BUT...

02:02.956 --> 02:05.500
HAVE YOUR NEW SHOW
ON OUR DESK

02:05.583 --> 02:06.876
BY NEXT MONDAY-- GOT IT?

02:08.002 --> 02:09.711
Bev Bighead:
OH, I CAN HARDLY WAIT

02:09.795 --> 02:14.050
{\an1}TO SEE OUR
LITTLE RALPHIE.

02:14.133 --> 02:15.510
OH, GREAT.

02:15.593 --> 02:18.388
{\an5}BUT WHY DID YOU
HAVE TO INVITE
THE LOSERS?

02:18.471 --> 02:20.014
Mrs. Bighead:
OH, ED

02:20.098 --> 02:23.143
THEY'RE OUR RALPHIE'S
BIGGEST FANS.

02:23.226 --> 02:24.853
{\an1}YOUR SON
IS A HUGE TALENT.

02:24.936 --> 02:28.523
IT'S A SHAME THERE WON'T BE
ANY MORE <i> FATHEADS</i> EPISODES.

02:28.606 --> 02:31.985
OH, BOYS, THERE
WILL ALWAYS BE RE-RUNS.

02:32.068 --> 02:33.194
HERE HE COMES NOW.

02:35.572 --> 02:37.198
All:
WELCOME HOME, RALPH!

02:44.330 --> 02:46.749
SOMETHING THE MATTER, DEAR?

02:46.833 --> 02:48.835
{\an1}OH, THEY'RE FORCING ME
TO MAKE A NEW SHOW.

02:48.918 --> 02:50.753
{\an1}I DON'T WANT
TO MAKE A NEW SHOW.

02:50.837 --> 02:53.173
HE DOESN'T WANT
TO MAKE A NEW SHOW.

02:53.256 --> 02:54.257
{\an1}I WANTED
TO PURSUE MY DREAM.

02:54.340 --> 02:58.636
{\an1}I WANTED TO SCULPT
THE WORLD'S LARGEST STILL LIFE.

02:58.720 --> 03:00.513
{\an1}NOW, I'LL NEVER
GET TO DO IT.

03:00.597 --> 03:04.517
{\an4}Rocko:
WHAT WILL YOUR NEW SHOW
BE ABOUT, MR. RALPH BIGHEAD?

03:04.601 --> 03:06.477
I HAVE NO IDEA.

03:06.561 --> 03:07.312
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

03:07.395 --> 03:10.940
CREATING AN IDEA
FOR AN ANIMATED SHOW

03:11.024 --> 03:12.275
MUST BE SO EASY.

03:12.358 --> 03:15.028
{\an1}OH, HEFF,
YOU KNOW NOTHING ABOUT IT.

03:15.111 --> 03:17.238
NO, REALLY, I'LL SHOW YOU.

03:17.322 --> 03:19.866
IT COULD BE ABOUT, UH, HMM...

03:20.867 --> 03:22.243
DELI MEATS!

03:22.327 --> 03:23.286
HELLO, MR. BOLOGNA.

03:23.369 --> 03:27.081
(<i> gasps</i> )
LOOK OUT FOR MR. BUTCHER KNIFE!

03:27.165 --> 03:29.167
OH, NO, GET AWAY FROM ME!

03:29.250 --> 03:30.376
(<i> screaming</i> )

03:30.460 --> 03:30.919
(<i> laughing</i> )

03:31.002 --> 03:33.463
HEY, HOME SLICE...

03:33.546 --> 03:35.798
HEFF, THAT'S THE STUPIDEST THING
I'VE EVER HEARD.

03:35.882 --> 03:38.176
AN IDEA LIKE THAT

03:38.259 --> 03:42.055
WOULD GET RALPH
KICKED OUT OF HIS CONTRACT.

03:43.222 --> 03:43.973
WHAT WAS THAT?

03:44.057 --> 03:47.727
I SAID THAT AN IDEA LIKE THAT

03:47.810 --> 03:49.562
WOULD GET YOU
KICKED OUT

03:49.646 --> 03:50.772
OF YOUR CONTRACT.

03:53.232 --> 03:55.151
I THINK YOU'VE
GOT YOUR FINGER

03:55.234 --> 03:56.486
ON THE PULSE
OF AMERICA.

03:56.569 --> 03:57.779
I DO?

03:57.862 --> 03:59.697
{\an1}HOW WOULD YOU
AND YOUR LITTLE FRIENDS

03:59.781 --> 04:00.615
{\an1}LIKE TO HELP ME
CREATE MY NEW SHOW?

04:00.698 --> 04:01.741
REALLY?

04:01.824 --> 04:04.369
WE COULD
HELP?

04:04.452 --> 04:05.995
{\an1}EXCUSE ME.

04:06.079 --> 04:07.330
SON...

04:07.413 --> 04:08.414
ARE YOU CRAZY?!

04:08.498 --> 04:10.166
{\an1}ASKING THOSE IDIOTS
TO HELP?!

04:10.249 --> 04:11.417
THEY'LL RUIN IT!

04:11.501 --> 04:14.504
EXACTLY. IF I LET
THEM DO MY NEW SHOW

04:14.587 --> 04:15.380
IT'LL BE A FAILURE.

04:15.463 --> 04:18.007
THEY'LL HAVE TO LET ME
OUT OF MY CONTRACT

04:18.091 --> 04:19.132
AND THEN I'LL BE FREE.

04:19.216 --> 04:20.426
I DON'T KNOW, ROCK.

04:20.510 --> 04:21.177
THIS SOUNDS LIKE WORK.

04:21.260 --> 04:24.180
YEAH, AND WE
DON'T KNOW ANYTHING

04:24.263 --> 04:26.599
ABOUT MAKING
ANIMATED CARTOONS.

04:26.683 --> 04:28.851
BUT, GUYS, THINK OF ALL THE JOY
RALPH BIGHEAD'S WORK

04:28.935 --> 04:31.270
HAS BROUGHT TO OUR LIVES.

04:31.354 --> 04:32.313
HE NEEDS OUR HELP.

04:32.397 --> 04:33.481
HOW CAN WE SAY NO?

04:33.564 --> 04:36.109
{\an1}SO HOW ABOUT IT, GUYS--
CAN YOU HELP ME OUT?

04:36.192 --> 04:39.112
{\an5}WELL, OKAY...

04:36.192 --> 04:39.112
WELL, OKAY...

04:39.195 --> 04:41.197
All:
WE'LL DO IT!

04:43.491 --> 04:44.951
(<i> tires screeching</i> )

04:45.034 --> 04:46.369
HERE'S YOUR BUDGET.

04:46.452 --> 04:48.246
TRY NOT TO SPEND
THE WHOLE THING.

04:48.329 --> 04:48.997
{\an1}AND HERE,
THIS WILL TELL YOU

04:49.080 --> 04:50.581
{\an1}ANYTHING
YOU WANT TO KNOW.

04:50.665 --> 04:56.921
{\an5}Rocko:
<i>7,291 SIMPLE STEPS</i>
<i>TO MAKING AN ANIMATED CARTOON.</i>

04:58.423 --> 05:00.466
{\an1}WELL, LET'S
MAKE A CARTOON.

05:02.343 --> 05:06.014
STEP ONE: DESIGN THE CHARACTERS.

05:06.097 --> 05:08.391
OKAY, HERE'S MY CHARACTER.

05:08.474 --> 05:10.143
HIS NAME IS SAL LAMI.

05:10.226 --> 05:11.477
{\an3}GET IT?

05:11.561 --> 05:13.396
SAL LAMI-- SALAMI.

05:13.479 --> 05:14.647
THIS IS BETTY BOLOGNA.

05:14.731 --> 05:17.567
SHE'S A GIRL.

05:17.650 --> 05:21.612
{\an1}OKAY, THIS CUTE
LITTLE GUY I CALL

05:21.696 --> 05:24.407
LESTER ROQUEFORT.

05:24.490 --> 05:25.491
Heffer:
LET ME SEE.

05:25.575 --> 05:28.327
WOW, THAT LOOKS
TERRIFIC, FILB.

05:28.411 --> 05:29.037
YEAH, THIS IS GREAT!

05:29.120 --> 05:32.040
CAN I MAKE
ONE LITTLE CHANGE?

05:32.123 --> 05:33.416
WELL...

05:33.499 --> 05:34.667
SURE.

05:34.751 --> 05:37.670
I THINK IT SHOULD BE
MORE LIKE THIS.

05:37.754 --> 05:40.882
AND WE COULD JUST
CALL HIM MR. CHEESE.

05:42.300 --> 05:44.886
Rocko:
NOW WE NEED TO WRITE THE SHOW.

05:44.969 --> 05:48.056
OKAY, LET'S SEE
WHAT WE'VE GOT SO FAR.

05:48.139 --> 05:51.768
{\an1}YOU SEEN
<i>ROBO-FROG V</i> YET?

05:51.851 --> 05:52.852
YEAH, IT'S OKAY.

05:52.935 --> 05:55.271
{\an5}Rocko:
OKAY, WE OPEN UP
THE SHOW IN THE MORNING.

05:55.354 --> 05:57.356
BETTY BOLOGNA WAKES UP
IN THE DELI.

05:57.440 --> 06:00.902
THEN SHE SAYS,
"OH, WHAT A BEAUTIFUL DAY!"

06:00.985 --> 06:02.862
{\an1}THE DOORBELL RINGS
AND SHE GOES TO THE...

06:02.945 --> 06:04.614
{\an1}Heffer:
TELEPHONE!

06:04.697 --> 06:05.782
EXCUSE ME?

06:05.865 --> 06:07.658
TELEPHONE,
THE TELEPHONE RINGS.

06:07.742 --> 06:10.328
{\an1}IT'S MUCH FUNNIER THAT WAY,
DON'T YOU THINK?

06:10.411 --> 06:13.372
{\an1}OH, YES, DEFINITELY
MUCH FUNNIER.

06:17.460 --> 06:19.128
{\an5}YEAH, FUNNY...

06:17.460 --> 06:19.128
TELEPHONES ARE FUNNY.

06:19.212 --> 06:21.214
{\an5}CARTOONS ARE FUN.

06:19.212 --> 06:21.214
...TELEPHONE.

06:21.297 --> 06:23.800
OKAY, SO THE <i> TELEPHONE</i> RINGS

06:23.883 --> 06:25.802
AND IT'S MR. CHEESE
ON THE PHONE.

06:25.885 --> 06:27.053
AND THE CHEESE SAYS,
"HELLO, BETTY.

06:27.136 --> 06:28.763
DO YOU WANT TO COME OVER?"

06:28.846 --> 06:30.723
AND THEN...

06:30.807 --> 06:31.724
{\an1}Heffer:
THE SALAMI.

06:31.808 --> 06:32.975
WHAT?

06:33.059 --> 06:33.768
SALAMI.

06:33.851 --> 06:36.813
IT SHOULD BE
SAL LAMI ON THE PHONE

06:36.896 --> 06:39.065
AND HE SAYS,
"I HATE BOLOGNA!"

06:39.148 --> 06:41.859
{\an1}AND THEN HE ATTACKS HER
THROUGH THE PHONE.

06:41.943 --> 06:43.861
(<i> laughing</i> )

06:43.945 --> 06:44.779
WAIT A MINUTE.

06:44.862 --> 06:47.448
THE SALAMI AIN'T
THE ONLY CHARACTER.

06:47.532 --> 06:49.325
WHY CAN'T THE CHEESE SAY IT?

06:49.408 --> 06:51.077
THE CHEESE WOULDN'T SAY THAT.

06:51.160 --> 06:52.370
HOW WOULD YOU KNOW?

06:52.453 --> 06:53.538
I'M THE CHEESE.

06:53.621 --> 06:56.290
{\an1}I KNOW WHAT HE SAYS
AND DON'T SAYS.

06:56.374 --> 06:57.625
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU?

06:57.708 --> 06:59.460
YOU'RE THE ONE
BEING DIFFICULT.

06:59.544 --> 07:00.753
{\an5}I MEAN, GOSH...

06:59.544 --> 07:00.753
{\an1}YOU EAT
ENOUGH OF IT.

07:00.837 --> 07:02.755
Rocko:
GUYS!

07:02.839 --> 07:03.506
WE'LL JUST PUT DOWN

07:03.589 --> 07:06.592
EITHER SALAMI OR CHEESE FOR NOW.

07:06.676 --> 07:08.052
WE'VE GOT TO MOVE ON.

07:08.136 --> 07:09.428
{\an4}SURE.

07:08.136 --> 07:09.428
FINE, WHATEVER.

07:09.512 --> 07:12.056
{\an5}I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

07:09.512 --> 07:12.056
BOY, CRABBY.

07:12.140 --> 07:15.893
SO, AFTER THE TELEPHONE RINGS,
AND SHE ANSWERS, THE...

07:15.977 --> 07:17.895
(<i> burping</i> )

07:17.979 --> 07:19.981
(<i> laughing</i> )

07:20.064 --> 07:21.190
EXCUSE ME.

07:21.274 --> 07:22.400
(<i> giggling</i> )

07:22.483 --> 07:24.819
{\an1}HEY, YOU COULD DO THAT
ON THE SHOW.

07:24.902 --> 07:27.405
IT WOULD BE GREAT!

07:27.488 --> 07:30.491
{\an1}YEAH, AND BOOGERS
CAN FLY OUT OF MY NOSE!

07:30.575 --> 07:32.034
(<i> laughing</i> )

07:32.118 --> 07:34.328
{\an1}YEAH, AND ALL THAT STUFF
CAN FLY ONTO BETTY.

07:34.412 --> 07:38.207
ALL THIS GOOP
AND SLIME AND SCUM...

07:38.291 --> 07:41.085
{\an5}Filburt:
...UP AND DOWN, LIKE
A LITTLE SALAMI...

07:41.169 --> 07:43.087
GOOGIE, GOOGIE,
GOOGIE, GOOGIE...

07:43.171 --> 07:47.133
{\an5}Heffer:
AND THE CHEESE JUST...
(<i> makes squishing noise</i> )

07:47.216 --> 07:49.177
OKAY!

07:49.260 --> 07:51.137
SO, BETTY
WAKES UP AND SAYS

07:51.220 --> 07:53.055
{\an1}(<i> straining</i> ):
"OH, WHAT A BEAUTIFUL DAY."

07:53.139 --> 07:54.849
AND THEN THE TELEPHONE...

07:54.932 --> 07:56.350
OR DOORBELL.

07:56.434 --> 08:00.313
...OR DOORBELL RINGING,
AND SHE ANSWERS IT

08:00.396 --> 08:01.480
AND SAYS HELLO.

08:01.564 --> 08:01.898
AND THEN THE SALAMI...

08:01.981 --> 08:04.692
{\an1}OR CHEESE.

08:04.775 --> 08:06.569
<i>...OR CHEESE</i>

08:06.652 --> 08:08.988
SAYS, "I HATE BOLOGNA"

08:09.071 --> 08:11.240
AND ATTACKS HER
THROUGH THE PHONE

08:11.324 --> 08:13.576
AND STUFF
COMES OUT OF HIS MOUTH

08:13.659 --> 08:14.911
