12:08.602 --> 12:10.438
HELLO?

12:10.521 --> 12:13.941
{\an5}WHAT A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

12:10.521 --> 12:13.941
I AM THE BEST CHARACTER...

12:14.024 --> 12:14.942
(<i> meow</i> )

12:15.025 --> 12:16.652
<i>THE MEAT LOAF SHOULD BE SPONGY</i>

12:16.735 --> 12:18.112
{\an5}<i>YET FIRM.</i>

12:16.735 --> 12:18.112
(<i> yodeling</i> )

12:19.738 --> 12:21.323
SALAMI, BETTER THAN THE BOLOGNA

12:21.407 --> 12:23.826
BETTER THAN THE...

12:23.909 --> 12:24.827
<i>EMBRACE IT.</i>

12:24.910 --> 12:26.745
(<i> yelling in distance</i> )

12:31.000 --> 12:33.377
SO, WHAT DID YOU THINK?

12:37.631 --> 12:40.843
WE LOVE IT!

12:58.444 --> 13:01.864
{\an5}Newsreel announcer:
<i>Wacky Delly</i> is the kids'
new favorite.

13:01.947 --> 13:04.283
Ratings off the counter
for <i> Wacky Delly.</i>

13:04.366 --> 13:07.369
These slices are
Hollowood's hot new stars.

13:07.453 --> 13:09.205
And now,
another O-Town

13:09.288 --> 13:10.581
news editorial
review.

13:10.664 --> 13:12.625
<i>Wacky Delly</i>
is degrading garbage.

13:12.708 --> 13:14.376
Its confused social morals

13:14.460 --> 13:17.379
{\an5}and disturbing undertones

13:14.460 --> 13:17.379
(<i> farting</i> )

13:17.463 --> 13:20.633
are tormenting the youths
of our nation.

13:20.716 --> 13:22.593
Kids everywhere are mindlessly

13:22.676 --> 13:24.637
imitating <i> Wacky Delly</i> antics:

13:24.720 --> 13:26.388
In Garberville, California;

13:26.472 --> 13:28.599
In Ogallala, Nebraska.

13:28.682 --> 13:32.102
For gosh sakes,
we've got to stop the carnage!

13:32.186 --> 13:33.395
FRANK?

13:33.479 --> 13:35.856
{\an1}DID YOU SEE
ALL THOSE KIDS' FACES?

13:35.940 --> 13:37.816
I KNOW.

13:37.900 --> 13:39.902
{\an1}DO RALPH
AND HIS BOYS KNOW

13:39.985 --> 13:41.529
THEY'VE CREATED
A MONSTER HERE?

13:41.612 --> 13:44.240
THEY DON'T HAVE A CLUE.

13:44.323 --> 13:45.324
{\an1}FRANK?

13:45.407 --> 13:46.200
YES, WILL?

13:46.283 --> 13:50.871
WE'VE GOT ONE HECK
OF A HIT SHOW HERE!

13:50.955 --> 13:52.206
YES!

13:52.289 --> 13:55.000
(<i> both laughing</i> )

13:59.922 --> 14:02.216
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

14:02.299 --> 14:05.511
THE SHOW IS ACTUALLY POPULAR.

14:08.847 --> 14:12.893
I'LL NEVER BE ABLE
TO CREATE MY MASTERPIECE.

14:12.977 --> 14:16.355
I MUST... GET OUT...
OF MY CONTRACT.

14:17.523 --> 14:21.068
I MUST SABOTAGE THE SHOW!

14:23.237 --> 14:25.698
WHY DON'T WE PUT
IN THAT DOWN SHOT?

14:25.781 --> 14:27.783
LET'S NOT,
AND SAY WE DID.

14:29.159 --> 14:29.785
HEY, FELLAS.

14:29.868 --> 14:33.122
{\an1}HOW'S EVERYTHING
COMING ALONG?

14:33.205 --> 14:36.000
JUST GREAT, R.B.,
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE A LOOK

14:36.083 --> 14:38.335
AT THE NEWEST
EPISODE?

14:39.878 --> 14:42.214
(<i> Heffer giggling wildly</i> )

14:43.340 --> 14:44.383
WHAT DO YOU
THINK?

14:44.466 --> 14:45.634
MMM...

14:45.718 --> 14:47.344
IT NEEDS SOMETHING.

14:47.428 --> 14:49.972
HOW ABOUT...

14:50.055 --> 14:51.098
MAYONNAISE?

14:52.224 --> 14:53.851
UH... MAYONNAISE?

14:53.934 --> 14:57.271
{\an1}YEAH, WHAT IF WE HOLD
ON A BUCKET OF MAYONNAISE

14:57.354 --> 14:59.106
FOR AN ENTIRE TEN MINUTES?

15:00.899 --> 15:03.319
{\an1}WELL, UH...
I DON'T KNOW.

15:03.402 --> 15:06.822
{\an1}DON'T YOU THINK IT STANDS
WELL ENOUGH ON ITS OWN?

15:06.905 --> 15:08.949
WHOSE SHOW IS IT?

15:09.033 --> 15:10.284
YOUR SHOW?

15:10.367 --> 15:11.160
I'M THE GENIUS HERE.

15:11.243 --> 15:14.788
{\an1}IF I WANT MAYONNAISE,
I GET MAYONNAISE!

15:14.872 --> 15:16.165
(<i> chuckling nervously</i> )

15:16.248 --> 15:18.667
YES, SIR.

15:18.751 --> 15:20.669
♪<i> Wacky Delly,</i> yeah! ♪

15:20.753 --> 15:21.003
♪<i> Wacky Delly,</i> yeah! ♪

15:25.507 --> 15:31.930
(<i> slow music playing</i> )

15:32.014 --> 15:34.725
Newsreel announcer:
<i>Delly</i> scores again!

15:34.808 --> 15:36.977
Powerful Warholian tribute!

15:37.061 --> 15:37.936
Fans go nuts!

15:42.107 --> 15:44.485
(<i> crowd clamoring</i> )

15:44.568 --> 15:45.819
(<i> tires screech</i> )

15:45.903 --> 15:49.531
HEY! IT'S RALPH BIGHEAD!

15:49.615 --> 15:51.200
IT'S HIM.

15:51.283 --> 15:52.951
CREATOR OF <i> WACKY DELLY.</i>

15:57.790 --> 16:00.084
I GOT HIS SHIRT.

16:00.167 --> 16:02.044
I GOT ONE OF HIS TIRES.

16:02.127 --> 16:05.089
I GOT A TREMENDOUS CHUNK
OF HIS SCALP.

16:05.172 --> 16:07.216
(<i> machinery whirring</i> )

16:07.299 --> 16:08.384
(<i> laughing</i> )

16:08.467 --> 16:10.469
WHOO!

16:12.012 --> 16:13.681
{\an1}OKAY, I'M FINISHED
SHOOTING.

16:13.764 --> 16:14.890
{\an1}LET'S GET
THIS BABY DEVELOPED.

16:14.973 --> 16:18.644
WE HAVE TO TAKE THE FILM
OUT OF THE CAMERA

16:18.727 --> 16:20.729
AND PUT IT IN THE FILM CAN.

16:20.813 --> 16:22.856
Filburt:
HIT THE LIGHTS.

16:24.108 --> 16:25.818
OKAY, I GOT THE FILM.

16:25.901 --> 16:27.236
I NEED THE CAN.

16:27.319 --> 16:27.986
{\an1}Heffer:
I GOT IT!

16:28.070 --> 16:31.198
(<i> can clatters, cat squeals</i> )

16:31.281 --> 16:32.741
HEY, THAT'S NOT IT!

16:32.825 --> 16:34.535
<i>OH, I DROPPED IT!</i>

16:34.618 --> 16:35.244
<i>OOPS, SORRY.</i>

16:35.327 --> 16:37.287
{\an1}<i>WILL YOU QUIT</i>
<i>GRABBING ME</i>

16:37.371 --> 16:38.706
<i>AND TURN ON</i>
<i>THE LIGHTS?!</i>

16:38.789 --> 16:40.207
<i>I SAID I WAS SORRY.</i>

16:40.290 --> 16:41.625
<i>TURN ON THE LIGHTS!</i>

16:41.709 --> 16:44.420
{\an5}<i>THAT'LL EXPOSE</i>
<i>THE FILM,</i>
<i>EISENSTEIN!</i>

16:44.503 --> 16:46.088
<i>JUST GIVE IT TO ME.</i>

16:46.171 --> 16:47.339
<i>OUCH, STOP IT.</i>

16:47.423 --> 16:49.007
I DON'T
UNDERSTAND, HEFFER.

16:49.091 --> 16:50.759
YOU'RE ALWAYS
SPITTING ON ME.

16:50.843 --> 16:51.927
Rocko:
GUYS...

16:52.010 --> 16:53.095
(<i> screams</i> ):
GUYS!

16:55.305 --> 16:56.598
HEY, GUYS.

16:56.682 --> 16:57.599
HOW'S IT GOING?

16:57.683 --> 17:01.395
HEY, I FOUND IT!

17:01.478 --> 17:04.189
I FOUND IT!

17:04.272 --> 17:05.107
OOPS.
I DIDN'T SABOTAGE...

17:05.190 --> 17:08.484
I MEAN, I DIDN'T EXPOSE
THE FILM, DID I?

17:08.569 --> 17:09.737
ISN'T THAT
THE NEXT <i> WACKY DELLY?</i>

17:09.819 --> 17:12.531
I GUESS WE'LL
HAVE TO SHOOT

17:12.614 --> 17:14.282
{\an1}THE WHOLE THING
OVER AGAIN.

17:14.366 --> 17:15.576
NONSENSE, JUST RUN IT
THE WAY IT IS.

17:15.659 --> 17:18.871
BUT IT'S OVEREXPOSED.

17:18.954 --> 17:21.749
{\an4}Ralph:
TRUST ME,
IT'LL BE GREAT.

17:24.710 --> 17:29.882
"RALPH BIGHEAD SCORES BIG
WITH OVEREXPOSED EPISODE.

17:29.965 --> 17:32.468
TOTAL GENIUS"?!

17:32.551 --> 17:33.594
(<i> groans</i> )

17:33.677 --> 17:36.513
(<i> crowd clamoring</i> )

17:42.102 --> 17:45.731
{\an4}Man:
OOH, OOH, HERE HE COMES,
HERE HE COMES!

17:45.814 --> 17:47.900
(<i> crashing</i> )

17:55.824 --> 17:59.286
(<i> Bev laughing hysterically</i> )

18:01.872 --> 18:04.875
Bev:
EDDIE, EDDIE, EDDIE...

18:04.958 --> 18:07.544
(<i> laughing</i> )

18:09.087 --> 18:10.839
(<i> doorbell chimes</i> )

18:13.592 --> 18:16.512
RALPH, I'M SO GLAD
YOU DROPPED BY.

18:16.595 --> 18:18.722
GIVE YOUR OLD MAN A HUG.

18:19.932 --> 18:21.517
DAD, I NEED YOUR HELP.

18:21.600 --> 18:24.561
ROCKO AND HIS FRIENDS
ARE RUINING MY LIFE.

18:24.645 --> 18:26.855
(<i> Bev laughing</i> )

18:27.689 --> 18:30.692
ROCKO PROBLEMS, HMM?

18:30.776 --> 18:34.571
{\an1}WELL, LET ME SHOW YOU A LITTLE
OF WHAT I'VE BEEN UP TO.

18:36.406 --> 18:39.910
WE'RE REALLY CLOSE TO
SOME MAJOR BREAKTHROUGHS

18:39.993 --> 18:41.995
IN ROCKO RESEARCH.

18:44.498 --> 18:46.208
THIS IS IT, SON.

18:46.291 --> 18:49.211
THE HEAT RAY!

18:49.294 --> 18:51.380
WITH THIS DEVICE

18:51.463 --> 18:53.841
{\an1}I'LL BE ABLE TO RID
MY LIFE OF ROCKO

18:53.924 --> 18:56.176
AND HIS MEDDLING FRIENDS
FOREVER.

18:56.260 --> 18:58.804
NO MORE BASEBALLS
ON THE FRONT LAWN

18:58.887 --> 19:03.392
NO MORE SPUNKY
IN MY SALMON BUSHES.

19:07.062 --> 19:10.649
BEST OF ALL, NO MORE ROCKO!

19:10.732 --> 19:13.151
(<i> laughing</i> )

19:13.235 --> 19:16.321
{\an1}BUT, DAD, I JUST WANT
TO GET RID OF THE STUDIO

19:16.405 --> 19:17.739
AND <i> WACKY DELLY.</i>

19:17.823 --> 19:19.825
I DON'T WANT TO HURT ROCKO.

19:21.910 --> 19:24.246
OH.

19:24.329 --> 19:27.416
WELL, IN THAT CASE,
IF MY CALCULATIONS ARE CORRECT

19:27.499 --> 19:30.502
WE JUST FIRE A BEAM 35 DEGREES
NORTH BY NORTHWEST.

19:30.586 --> 19:34.256
{\an1}AFTER REFRACTING OFF ONE OF
MY ROCKO SURVEILLANCE SATELLITES

19:34.339 --> 19:37.593
{\an1}THIS SPLIT BEAM SHOULD STRIKE
THE EARTH'S POLAR CAPS.

19:37.676 --> 19:40.220
THE MELTED ICE
SHOULD SEND A WALL OF WATER

19:40.304 --> 19:41.597
STRAIGHT FOR HOLLOWOOD

19:41.680 --> 19:44.933
{\an1}ERASING BIGHEAD STUDIOS
AND <i> WACKY DELLY...</i>

19:45.017 --> 19:45.767
(<i> laughing</i> )

19:45.851 --> 19:49.396
FROM EXISTENCE!

19:49.479 --> 19:50.188
THANKS, DAD.

19:59.781 --> 20:01.199
(<i> beeping</i> )

20:04.745 --> 20:07.289
Heffer:
♪ WACKY DELLY, YEAH ♪

20:07.372 --> 20:08.040
♪ WACKY DELLY, YEAH ♪

20:08.123 --> 20:10.792
♪ SAL AND CHEESE ARE GOOD... ♪

20:10.876 --> 20:12.461
(<i> explosion</i> )

20:26.308 --> 20:28.477
(<i> grunting</i> )

20:48.121 --> 20:49.915
HEY!

20:51.291 --> 20:56.797
{\an1}"FLOOD DESTROYS ALL SHOWS
EXCEPT <i> WACKY DELLY"?!</i>

20:56.880 --> 20:59.174
(<i> groans</i> ):
OH!

21:02.177 --> 21:05.263
(<i> crowd clamoring</i> )

21:05.347 --> 21:06.390
IT'S HIM!

21:06.473 --> 21:06.682
IT'S HIM!

21:06.765 --> 21:08.433
HELLO!

21:13.271 --> 21:14.523
THAT SHOW IS JUST GENIUS.

21:14.606 --> 21:17.234
SUPERB.

21:24.449 --> 21:25.867
{\an1}Rocko:
OH, R.B.

21:25.951 --> 21:27.703
WE WERE JUST
TALKING ABOUT YOU.

21:27.786 --> 21:30.288
{\an1}AFTER YOU FINISHED EATING
THAT <i> FATHEADS</i> EPISODE

21:30.372 --> 21:34.418
{\an1}WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE
THIS WEEK'S <i> WACKY DELLY?</i>

21:35.043 --> 21:39.047
(<i> gagging, coughing</i> )

21:39.131 --> 21:42.884
CAN'T YOU SEE THAT
I HATE THIS SHOW

21:42.968 --> 21:45.595
AND I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO SABOTAGE IT

21:45.679 --> 21:46.888
SINCE DAY ONE?

21:46.972 --> 21:50.225
BUT YOU KEEP
MESSING ME UP.

21:50.308 --> 21:52.561
I WANT TO GET OUT
OF THIS BUSINESS

21:52.644 --> 21:54.187
AND MAKE <i> REAL</i> ART.

21:54.271 --> 21:57.566
{\an1}GEE, R.B., I THINK
YOU GOT IT ALL WRONG.

21:57.649 --> 22:00.652
{\an1}YOU'VE BEEN AFFORDED
A GREAT OPPORTUNITY HERE:

22:00.736 --> 22:03.155
{\an1}RUNNING YOUR VERY OWN
ANIMATION SERIES.

22:03.238 --> 22:04.698
AND EVERYBODY LOVES IT.

22:04.781 --> 22:06.199
IT'S YOUR ART.

22:06.283 --> 22:10.037
DON'T FLEE YOUR SITUATION,
EMBRACE IT.

22:10.120 --> 22:12.289
{\an1}YOU SHOULD BE TRYING
TO MAKE THIS SHOW

22:12.372 --> 22:14.791
THE BEST DARN SHOW
IT CAN POSSIBLY BE.

22:14.875 --> 22:18.420
{\an1}YOU SHOULD BE THE BEST
RALPH BIGHEAD YOU CAN BE!

22:19.671 --> 22:21.882
YEAH, ROCKO.

22:21.965 --> 22:24.760
YEAH, ROCKO.

22:24.843 --> 22:26.595
YEAH, ROCKO.

22:26.678 --> 22:27.721
YEAH, ROCKO!

22:27.804 --> 22:30.140
I'M GOING TO DO IT!

22:30.223 --> 22:33.935
I'M GOING TO MAKE
THE BEST DARN SHOW

22:34.019 --> 22:36.938
THIS WORLD HAS EVER SEEN!

22:38.482 --> 22:39.775
And now,
the newest episode

22:39.858 --> 22:41.526
of <i> Wacky Delly.</i>

22:41.610 --> 22:46.948
{\an1}(<i> "Chinese Dance" from</i>
The Nutcracker <i> playing</i> )

22:47.032 --> 22:49.576
(<i> buzzer sounds</i> )

22:49.659 --> 22:52.621
{\an1}Newsreel announcer:
<i>Wacky Delly</i> canceled.

22:52.704 --> 22:53.497
Highbrow meat goes bad.

22:59.377 --> 23:00.796
(<i> tires screech</i> )

23:04.508 --> 23:06.843
(<i> screaming</i> ):
YOU CRETINS!

23:06.927 --> 23:08.970
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT ART IS!

23:09.054 --> 23:10.430
I'LL SHOW YOU!

23:13.183 --> 23:18.396
(<i> country music playing</i> )

23:33.995 --> 23:35.455
OH, DEAR GOSH.

23:35.539 --> 23:39.501
LET THIS NOT BE
ANOTHER DELIRIOUS ILLUSION.

23:39.584 --> 23:40.794
CAN IT BE?

23:40.877 --> 23:46.341
CAN IT BE THAT I HAVE FINALLY
FINISHED MY LIFE'S MASTERWORK?

23:46.424 --> 23:48.510
BEHOLD!

23:48.593 --> 23:52.889
MY MASTERPIECE
IS COMPLETE.

23:52.973 --> 23:56.268
(<i> crying hysterically</i> )

23:56.935 --> 24:01.231
I'M SO HAPPY.

24:04.943 --> 24:06.194
HEY, NOT BAD.

24:06.278 --> 24:10.949
{\an1}BUT HAVE YOU SEEN
<i>WACKY DELLY?</i>

24:11.032 --> 24:13.201
THE FIRST SEASON,
THAT IS.

24:13.285 --> 24:16.413
BEFORE THAT
NEW GUY RUINED IT.

